<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd"><html>
<head>
<title>BUILD-KIVUNG-SPLINTER-GROUP-SEMANTIC-NETWORK</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Language" content="en-gb">
</head>
<body>
<h3><i>I build the semantic network of the leaders of a splinter group of the
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.oup.com/us/catalog/general/subject/Anthropology/SocialCultural/?view=usa&ci=9780198279815">
Pomio Kivung cult</a>. This adds new nodes the
<a href="BUILD-KIVUNG-SEMANTIC-NETWORK-V2.html">mainstream network</a>.</i></h3>
<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
<p><b>BUILD-KIVUNG-SPLINTER-GROUP-SEMANTIC-NETWORK</b></p>
<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
<pre>let mind-body-dualism one-of my-anchor-points with [my-name = "Mind-body dualism"]
let promiscuous-teleology one-of my-anchor-points with [my-name = "Promiscuous teleology"]
let hazard-precaution one-of my-anchor-points with [my-name = "Hazard precaution"]
let immanent-justice one-of my-anchor-points with [my-name = "Immanent justice"]
let god one-of my-nodes with [my-name = &quot;God&quot;]
let ancestors one-of my-nodes with [my-name = &quot;Ancestors&quot;]
let village-government one-of my-nodes with [my-name = &quot;Village Government&quot;]
let return-from-the-dead one-of my-nodes with [my-name = &quot;Return from the dead&quot;]
let time-bilong-kampani one-of my-nodes with [my-name = &quot;Time bilong kampani&quot;]
let taim-bilong-gavman one-of my-nodes with [my-name = &quot;Taim bilong Gavman&quot;]
<i>; now add the non-mainstream beliefs</i>
let ring-rituals make-belief-node-v2 "Ring rituals" 100 7 1 2 13
ask ring-rituals [set my-repeat-maximum 32] ; 8 months
link-nodes hazard-precaution ring-rituals
let mass-marriage make-belief-node-v2 "Mass marriage" 100 1 0 3 7
ask mass-marriage [set my-repeat-maximum 1]
link-nodes ring-rituals mass-marriage
let discarding-clothes make-belief-node-v2 "Discarding clothes" 50 1 0 6 14
link-nodes mass-marriage discarding-clothes
link-nodes ring-rituals ancestors
link-nodes ring-rituals return-from-the-dead
let round-house make-belief-node-v2 "Round house" 50 1 0 9 16
ask round-house [set my-repeat-maximum 10] ; "short duration"
link-nodes ring-rituals round-house
let feasts make-belief-node-v2 "Feasts" 80 30 0 13 15
ask feasts [set my-repeat-maximum 8]
link-nodes round-house feasts
let vigils-and-rituals-to-welcome-ancestors make-belief-node-v2 "Vigils &amp; rituals to welcome the ancestors" 50 1 0 11 13
ask vigils-and-rituals-to-welcome-ancestors [set my-repeat-maximum 10] ; "short duration"
link-nodes round-house vigils-and-rituals-to-welcome-ancestors
link-nodes feasts vigils-and-rituals-to-welcome-ancestors
link-nodes discarding-clothes vigils-and-rituals-to-welcome-ancestors
link-nodes ancestors vigils-and-rituals-to-welcome-ancestors
link-nodes return-from-the-dead vigils-and-rituals-to-welcome-ancestors
let black-skin-will-peel-away make-belief-node-v2 "Black skin will peel away" 40 1 0 15 14
link-nodes black-skin-will-peel-away vigils-and-rituals-to-welcome-ancestors
link-nodes promiscuous-teleology black-skin-will-peel-away 
link-nodes time-bilong-kampani black-skin-will-peel-away
let no-more-skin-soars make-belief-node-v2 "No more skin sores" 40 1 0 15 16
link-nodes hazard-precaution no-more-skin-soars 
link-nodes black-skin-will-peel-away no-more-skin-soars 
let spirit-possession make-belief-node-v2 "Spirit possession" 50 1 0 3 4
ask spirit-possession [set my-repeat-maximum 1]
link-nodes mind-body-dualism spirit-possession
link-nodes ancestors spirit-possession
let reports-in-temples make-belief-node-v2 "Reports in temples" 50 1 0 6 10
link-nodes reports-in-temples ancestors
link-nodes reports-in-temples return-from-the-dead
let devil-blocks-the-way make-belief-node-v2 "Devil blocks the way" 50 1 0 10 1
ask devil-blocks-the-way [set my-repeat-maximum 1]
link-nodes mind-body-dualism devil-blocks-the-way
link-nodes immanent-justice devil-blocks-the-way
link-nodes taim-bilong-gavman devil-blocks-the-way
link-nodes god devil-blocks-the-way
let tolai-will-be-punished make-belief-node-v2 "Tolai will be punished" 50 1 0 15 3
link-nodes immanent-justice tolai-will-be-punished
link-nodes taim-bilong-gavman tolai-will-be-punished
let wicked-tolai-will-squander-the-cargo make-belief-node-v2 "Wicked Tolai will squander the cargo" 50 1 0 20 5
link-nodes immanent-justice wicked-tolai-will-squander-the-cargo
link-nodes taim-bilong-gavman wicked-tolai-will-squander-the-cargo
let cargo-will-be-shared make-belief-node-v2 "Cargo will be shared" 50 1 0 22 9
link-nodes immanent-justice cargo-will-be-shared
link-nodes wicked-tolai-will-squander-the-cargo cargo-will-be-shared
let forest-will-be-flattened make-belief-node-v2 "Forest will be flattened" 50 1 0 20 13
link-nodes forest-will-be-flattened cargo-will-be-shared
link-nodes promiscuous-teleology forest-will-be-flattened
link-nodes time-bilong-kampani forest-will-be-flattened
let new-paradise make-belief-node-v2 "New Paradise" 50 1 0 18 8
link-nodes promiscuous-teleology new-paradise 
link-nodes taim-bilong-gavman new-paradise 
set my-non-mainstream-nodes 
   (turtle-set ring-rituals mass-marriage discarding-clothes round-house feasts vigils-and-rituals-to-welcome-ancestors 
               black-skin-will-peel-away no-more-skin-soars spirit-possession reports-in-temples devil-blocks-the-way
               tolai-will-be-punished wicked-tolai-will-squander-the-cargo cargo-will-be-shared forest-will-be-flattened new-paradise)
ask my-non-mainstream-nodes [set label-color red]
set my-nodes (turtle-set my-nodes my-non-mainstream-nodes my-anchor-points)
</pre>
<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>
<p><a href="BUILD-KIVUNG-SEMANTIC-NETWORK.html">BUILD-KIVUNG-SEMANTIC-NETWORK</a> 
builds the mainstream Pomio Kivung network.</p>
<h2>How this works</h2>
<p>This creates each node in
<a target="_blank" href="images/Kivung%20semantic%20network_splinter%20group.jpg">this diagram</a> and the 
links between them and the anchor points. The nodes coloured black are new 
nodes.</p>
<h2>History</h2>
<p>Ken Kahn implemented this on 3 August, 2010.
